<https://semiceu.github.io/StatDCAT-AP_Copy/release/3.0.0#rdfs:ResourceShape/05b5725a4102b08d4abd7a3293a752466207d9a4> rdfs:seeAlso "https://semiceu.github.io/StatDCAT-AP_Copy/release/3.0.0#Resource.unitofmeasurement";
  shacl:class skos:Concept;
  shacl:description """a unit of measurement of the observations in the dataset, for example Euro, square kilometre,
purchasing power standard (PPS), full-time equivalent, percentage. 
Unit of measurement is a conceptual entity that applies to all distribution formats,
e.g. in the case when a dataset is provided both in SDMX and in Data Cube."""@en;
  shacl:name "unit of measurement"@en;
  shacl:path <http://data.europa.eu/s1n/statUnitMeasure> .

<https://semiceu.github.io/StatDCAT-AP_Copy/release/3.0.0#rdfs:ResourceShape/58fd3e5699e0a40907c686ddd9ddc2439d715b6e> rdfs:seeAlso "https://semiceu.github.io/StatDCAT-AP_Copy/release/3.0.0#Resource.numberofdataseries";
  shacl:description "number of data series contained in the dataset"@en;
  shacl:minCount 1;
  shacl:name "number of data series"@en;
  shacl:path <http://data.europa.eu/s1n/numSeries> .

<https://semiceu.github.io/StatDCAT-AP_Copy/release/3.0.0#rdfs:ResourceShape/68c5eb8e0793d4958ff5dfb60cfdb18f0c77f5b1> rdfs:seeAlso "https://semiceu.github.io/StatDCAT-AP_Copy/release/3.0.0#Resource.attribute";
  shacl:class <http://purl.org/linked-data/cube#AttributeProperty>;
  shacl:description """a component used to qualify and interpret observed values, e.g. units of measure, any scaling factors and metadata such as the status of the observation (e.g. estimated, provisional).
Attribute is a conceptual entity that applies to all distribution formats, e.g. in case a dataset is provided both in SDMX and in DataCube."""@en;
  shacl:name "attribute"@en;
  shacl:path <http://data.europa.eu/s1n/attribute> .

<https://semiceu.github.io/StatDCAT-AP_Copy/release/3.0.0#rdfs:ResourceShape/705d3d050df964292af08292097fe05ded9edab6> rdfs:seeAlso "https://semiceu.github.io/StatDCAT-AP_Copy/release/3.0.0#Resource.unitofmeasurement";
